(# Configuration Examples) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository includes a few example JSON files under examples/ to help you get the training pipeline running quickly.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## dataset_roots.example.json) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use this as the starting point for local training runs. It includes:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- daic_woz_root) Tj
T*
(- meld_root) Tj
T*
(- ravdess_root) Tj
T*
(- manifest_dir) Tj
T*
(- ravdess_frames_dir) Tj
T*
(- comorbidity_balanced_manifest) Tj
T*
(- comorbidity_target_rows) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The comorbidity bootstrapped manifest now defaults to tmp_datasets/comorbidity_60k.csv, with comorbidity_target_rows set to 60000 and a balanced bucket target mix.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why that path:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- the repository had a locked data/manifests/comorbidity_balanced.csv file in this workspace) Tj
T*
(- tmp_datasets/ is writable and safe for regenerated pipeline artifacts) Tj
T*
(- the training pipeline and README now both point to that writable location by default) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## dataset_roots_and_federated.example.json) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use this when you want the same dataset roots plus a federated training example.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(It includes the same writable manifest path so federated and non-federated runs stay aligned.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Local Copies) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When you copy the examples to a local file, you can adjust the dataset roots and leave the writable manifest path as-is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Copy-Item examples\\dataset_roots.example.json examples\\dataset_roots.local.json) Tj
T*
(Copy-Item examples\\dataset_roots_and_federated.example.json examples\\dataset_roots_and_federated.local.json) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If the locked CSV issue is resolved later, you can point comorbidity_balanced_manifest back to data/manifests/comorbidity_balanced.csv, but that is no longer the default.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Notes on Current Training Priorities) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The training pipeline currently treats:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- text_transformer as the primary text bundle,) Tj
ET
endstream
